Who am I?


Since most of the content on this site is focused around me professionally, I'd like to offer this small section about some of my more personal details for those that would like to get to know me a bit more......During my first year of working for Johnson and Johnson as an Application Support Analyst, I started making the right connections and worked my way into a postion as a Salesforce Developer. Johnson and Johnson boasts a healthy portfolio of Salesforce instances. Thus, the great opportunity about working for them is that there are a wide array of projects to get into within the various sectors of J&J. However, the responsibilities and day-to-day work does not vary wildy as most project teams work in an agile framework to deliver business requested features within a given iteration. While being a good developer is helpful, J&J also places great value in effective communication. This can range from the abilty to relay roadblocks in current devlopment during standup, contributing to the technical design of a story in refinement, or framing demos appropriately to a non-technical audience.
